cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep neural network architectures for video classification, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various design choices and explores different architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) cells, which are a type of recurrent neural network, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes new methods for handling full-length videos, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
